error: field `orbit_target` is not classified: every field of application state must say which persistence artifacts it reaches, so that nothing is ever left out silently.

       Add one of:

           #[snapshot(settings)]  — a user preference outliving any one project; reaches the dump, not the document
           #[snapshot(document)]  — what the model IS; reaches the document, and so also the dump
           #[snapshot(view)]      — where you are working rather than what the model is; reaches the dump, not the document
           #[snapshot(session)]   — how the workspace was left, not what the user prefers; reaches the dump, not the document
           #[snapshot(transient)] — genuinely momentary; reaches neither artifact — justify it in review
           #[snapshot(derived)]   — reconstructible from classified state alone; reaches neither artifact

       `transient` and `derived` reach neither artifact and are the two ways to get this error to go away without deciding anything, so they are the ones review looks at. `derived` at least makes a checkable claim: dropping the field must change how long something takes and NOTHING else.

       The category describes this field's WHOLE object and does not recurse into it — serialization already carries what is inside. See docs/adr/0022.
  --> tests/compile_fail/several_unclassified_fields.rs:12:5
   |
12 |     orbit_target: [f32; 3],
   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^

